      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TRACY THE JET (9) was last season's top three-year-old filly having put together a string of wins including the Group 1 Victoria Oaks/Need For Speed double and also beat the boys in the rich Ascent in NZ in November. It's a new challenge stepping up against open company but she races well fresh and was readied with three trials. LOVEMETO NZ (10) won from a similar barrier last start, working forward to find the front before scoring easily. That continued some strong form that included a second to Keayang Zahara in the G1 Grand Prix three back. Could strike again. GOTFEELINGSYOUKNOW (5) was rewarded for his recent consistency with a Menangle win in a hit-and-run trip to Sydney last week. Gets the same draw and could deliver again. REMUS PHOENIX (7) draws wide but won at Melton four back and has placed in each start since, two of those behind Keayang Zahara at G1 level. KEAYANG STUKA (4) has won three of four fresh attempts and was readied with two trial placings. Keep safe.",
